On the International Day for the Elimination of Violence Against Women, the Vice President expresses deep concern about the widespread problem of violence against women. He highlights that approximately one in three women globally experience physical or sexual abuse, often at the hands of intimate partners. The Vice President also condemns practices such as human trafficking and forced marriage, which victimize women and girls. He emphasizes that violence against women perpetuates poverty and threatens peace, and ultimately degrades humanity. The Vice President calls for collective efforts to combat gender-based violence and all forms of abuse of power. He reaffirms the commitment of the United States to join the international community in this fight.